Credits: @tomjauncey.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Great Planet on August 08, 2021. May be an image of fire and sky.

node.text:
🇬🇷💔 Heartbreaking images of the spreading wildfire in Greece. Areas of Athens have recorded temperatures of 47-55 Celsius degrees, and the extreme temperatures and fire have left thousands with no option but to flee their homes. Our thoughts are with the victims and their families!

Credits:
1. @alexmaragos
2. Stavros Dem
3. @vangelis_magg
4. VPetsopoulos on Twitter
5. @kosmaskoumianos

node.text:
🌲 We admire cabins (obviously); the architecture, locations, and how unique each one is. But more so the idea of them: removed from the hustle as well as the community and memories built inside their walls. Where would your dream cabin be located? Alaska would be nice.

Credits: @sincerelysepe.

node.text:
🇮🇸 Iceland is truly a geological wonderland and the newly discovered Stuðlagil is probably one of the most beautiful basalt column attractions on the planet. 
If you visit this canyon at the right time, you will experience this incredible river colour. The ideal months to see this vibrant turquoise color is from mid-May to mid-July as that is when the dam is not overflowing. 

Credits: @h0rdur.
